This paper discusses the strategic behavior of agents in response to decision-making rules produced by algorithms, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the use of classifiers, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper touches on the issue of security and privacy in decision-making algorithms, which could fall under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper uses mathematical models to analyze the behavior of agents, which could also fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
